          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p>P. S. I suppose another cause for your<lb/> dislike <del>for</del>
                                        to lawyers is the fact that being six<lb/> months in arrears
                                        for rent of the "Israelite Office"<lb/> which you have now
                                        left, the lawyers have been called in by your landlord<lb/>
                                        to aid in the collection of the rent, &amp; if there<lb/>
                                        were no lawyers you would be "benefited" from<lb/> the
                                        effects of the law: Very true &amp; very right Dr<lb/> but
                                        in this case "justice will be <add>?</add>cuted"</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I would like to know Revd Sir, why<lb/> it was
                                        that <date>Saturday</date> the <date>Sabbath</date> of the
                                        Israelite<lb/> was the day set especially for the Rest to
                                        receive<lb/> a deputation of Israelites presenting a
                                        grievance<lb/> they desired to remedy which bore upon them
                                        as<lb/> Israelites; verily the President &amp; his cabinet
                                        could<lb/> not have had a greater esteem for those who
                                        would<lb/> thus openly violate their <date>Sabbath</date> by
                                        attending<lb/> to secular political affairs: No
                                        deputation<lb/> of Christians would have been received, or
                                        would<lb/> have presented themselves on their day of
                                        rest.<lb/> But I suppose you were too elated with the<lb/>
                                        honors thrust upon you &amp; much too busy to think<lb/> of
                                        the day:—</p>
                    </body>
